Abdominal sternites (
Figs. 10–11
) unmodified, sternites III–VI subequal in length, VII much longer, suture between VII and VIII barely marked.

Aedeagus (
Figs. 12–15
) stout, with narrowing and subtriangular apical part of median lobe; internal armature complex and darkly sclerotized; parameres free (i.e., not fused with median lobe) and slender, bearing apical and subapical setae.
